<subSubSection id="C31C65001901FFC66A8BA16E71BDFDDE" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1901FFC66A8BA16E7103FEB7" blockId="33.[189,303,265,291]" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
<heading id="D0F181E71901FFC66A8BA16E7103FEB7" bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66A8BA16E7103FEB7" bold="true" box="[189,303,265,291]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB9368B1901FFC66A8BA15F71BDFDDE" blockId="33.[189,1399,312,586]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
In the 
<typeStatus id="54BD88291901FFC66B3AA15F716CFEC6" box="[268,320,312,338]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D081901FFC66BE0A15F73A5FEC6" authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[470,905,312,338]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66BE0A15F73A5FEC6" box="[470,905,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
there is a headless specimen (
<specimenCount id="9D00FD021901FFC66EC8A15F7506FEC6" box="[1278,1322,312,338]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" type="female">
1 
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66F22A15F7506FEC6" bold="true" box="[1300,1322,312,338]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">♀</emphasis>
</specimenCount>
, “P.I.: Mindanao / 
<collectingRegion id="49C2F8691901FFC66B7AA13C71EAFEE1" box="[332,454,347,373]" country="Philippines" name="Bukidnon" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Bukidnon</collectingRegion>
. 
<quantity id="4CFE9B6E1901FFC66BE6A13C7201FEE1" box="[464,557,347,373]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.48" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" unit="m" value="1480.0">1480 m</quantity>
. / Mt. Katanglad / 
<date id="FFB8104B1901FFC6693EA13C7395FEE1" box="[776,953,347,373]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" value="1959-10-27" valueMax="1959-10-31" valueMin="1959-10-27">27–31.X.1959</date>
”; “L.W. Quate / Collector” (
<potCollectionCode id="595268851901FFC66F31A13C7573FEE1" box="[1287,1375,347,373]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">BPBM</potCollectionCode>
)), see 
<figureCitation id="133D2A0E1901FFC66AD9A118717CFE0D" box="[239,336,383,409]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="27.[189,232,1891,1917]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,892,1852]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[189,1399,892,1852]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Fig. 6. Habitus, lateral view. A. Sphegina (Asiosphegina) achaeta Hippa, van Steenis &amp; Mutin, 2015, holotype, Ƌ, Myanmar. B. S. (A.) achaeta, ♀, Myanmar. C. S. (A.) albolobata sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Vietnam. D. S. (A.) amplistylus sp. nov., holotype, Ƌ, Philippines. E. S. (A.) apicalis Shiraki, 1930, Ƌ, Taiwan. F. S. (A.) apicalis, ♀, Taiwan. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3830551" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3830551/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Fig. 6B</figureCitation>
. This female is not 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D081901FFC6687BA1187428FE0D" authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[589,1028,383,409]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC6687BA1187428FE0D" box="[589,1028,383,409]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Sphegina (Asiosphegina) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because the postpronotum is black (yellow in 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D081901FFC66BBEA1C47274FE28" authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[392,600,418,445]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66BBEA1C471BBFE29" box="[392,407,419,445]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66B90A1C571EFFE28" box="[422,451,418,444]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66BFCA1C57274FE28" box="[458,600,418,444]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the wing is hyaline (slightly infuscated in 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D081901FFC66E5CA1C47516FE28" authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[1130,1338,418,445]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66E5CA1C47455FE29" box="[1130,1145,419,445]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66EBFA1C57489FE28" box="[1161,1189,418,444]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66E9BA1C57516FE28" box="[1197,1338,418,444]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and tergum V has the posterior margin straight (incised in 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D081901FFC66964A1A07408FE74" authorityName=", Thompson" authorityYear="1999" box="[850,1060,454,481]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="177" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="philippina" subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66964A1A0734DFE75" box="[850,865,455,481]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66947A1A173A2FE74" box="[881,910,454,480]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC669A3A1A17408FE74" box="[917,1060,454,480]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">) philippina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). This specimen is possibly the female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C064D081901FFC66B5CA18D7260FD97" authority="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin, 2018" authorityName="Steenis &amp; Hippa &amp; Mutin" authorityYear="2018" box="[362,588,489,516]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Sphegina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="147" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplistylus" status="sp. nov." subGenus="Asiosphegina">
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66B5CA18D7155FD90" box="[362,377,490,516]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66BBDA18E718BFD97" box="[395,423,489,515]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">(A</emphasis>
.
<emphasis id="B972EA991901FFC66B99A18E7260FD97" box="[431,588,489,515]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">) amplistylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24157E21901FFC66860A18E729BFD97" box="[598,695,489,515]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but as even the males of all the similar species are very difficult to distinguish from each other without reference to genitalia, the identity of this female remains doubtful.
</paragraph>
